    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="4"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710.H Agenda/13</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Director General of the Pan American Union</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rowe</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-06">December 6,
                            1937</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I beg to send you herewith the
                    Report of the Subcommittee on Program and Regulations of the Eighth
                    International Conference of American States,<note n="3" xml:id="d4fn3">Eighth
                        International Conference of American States, Lima, Peru, <hi rend="italic"
                            >Project of Regulations Submitted to the Governments, members of the Pan
                            American Union by resolution adopted by the Governing Board on December
                            1, 1937</hi> (Washington, Pan American Union).</note> which was approved
                    by the Governing Board at the session of December first and to which is attached
                    a draft of regulations of the Eighth Conference.</p>
                <p>May I call your attention to the fact that the Report requests that any
                    observations which your Government may have to make be transmitted to the Pan
                    American Union on or before March 1, 1938.</p>
                <p>I beg to remain, my dear Mr. Secretary,</p>
                <p>Most sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. <hi rend="smallcaps">Rowe</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
